      "id": "bug-030",
      "timestamp": "2026-05-14T13:30:00.000Z",
      "error_message": "Dual-definition runtime strategy invalid for top-level const declarations — ANNUAL_CHECKUP and 6 other constants cannot be redeclared globally (SyntaxError: Identifier has already been declared)",
      "file": "index.html, src/utils/costEngine.js",
      "root_cause": "const/let bindings at the top level of a classic script are added to the global declarative record but cannot be re-declared. Loading costEngine.js first declares all 7 constants; the inline script re-declaring them with const would throw SyntaxError. function declarations are hoistable and silently overwrite — dual-definition is ONLY safe for function declarations, not const/let.",
      "fix": "Skipped dual-definition holding period for const declarations. Step C executed immediately after Step B, collapsing them into a single atomic operation for const-containing modules.",
      "tags": [
        "const-redeclaration",
        "classic-script",
        "dual-definition",
        "wave3",
        "costEngine"
      ],
